# React Integration & DM Feature Guide


## FIRST OF ALL

### Real-Time Messaging

Two WebSocket endpoints:
- `/ws` — SockJS (browser-compatible)
- `/ws-raw` — Raw WebSocket (Postman, mobile)

STOMP destination conventions:
- Client sends to: `/app/chat/{channelId}`
- Server broadcasts to: `/group/channel/{channelId}`

**Critical pattern — split pipeline**: messages are broadcast immediately to connected subscribers using a lightweight in-memory DTO, then persisted asynchronously via `@Async` to keep latency low. Do not collapse this into a single synchronous write.

A custom `WebSocketHandlerDecorator` normalizes STOMP null-byte frame terminators for Postman compatibility.

### Presence Tracking

Redis keys: `presence:user:<uuid>` → `"ONLINE"`, set/deleted by `WebSocketEventListener` on STOMP connect/disconnect. `PresenceService` uses Redis MGET for batch queries.

### Data Model

All entities use UUID primary keys. Key relationships:
- `Guild` → owns many `Channel`s and `GuildMember`s
- `Channel` → has many `Message`s
- `Message` → soft-deletable (`deleted_at`), supports thread replies (`reply_to_id`)
- `GuildMember` → join table for User ↔ Guild with `banned` flag



## Part 1 — React + SockJS Integration

### Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install sockjs-client @stomp/stompjs
```

> [!NOTE]
> `@stomp/stompjs` v7+ has built-in SockJS support. No need for the old `stompjs` package.

---

### 1. API Service — REST Calls

Create a simple helper for all your REST endpoints:

```js
// src/services/api.js

const BASE_URL = "http://localhost:8000/api/v1";

function getToken() {
  return localStorage.getItem("accessToken");
}

async function request(endpoint, options = {}) {
  const res = await fetch(`${BASE_URL}${endpoint}`, {
    ...options,
    headers: {
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
      Authorization: `Bearer ${getToken()}`,
      ...options.headers,
    },
  });

  if (!res.ok) {
    const error = await res.json().catch(() => ({}));
    throw new Error(error.message || `Request failed: ${res.status}`);
  }

  return res.json();
}

// ── Auth ──
export async function login(email, password) {
  return request("/auth/login", {
    method: "POST",
    body: JSON.stringify({ email, password }),
  });
}

export async function verifyOtp(email, otpCode) {
  const data = await request("/auth/verify-otp", {
    method: "POST",
    body: JSON.stringify({ email, otpCode }),
  });
  // Save tokens
  localStorage.setItem("accessToken", data.accessToken);
  localStorage.setItem("refreshToken", data.refreshToken);
  return data;
}

// ── Channels ──
export async function getGuildChannels(guildId) {
  return request(`/channels/${guildId}`);
}

// ── Messages ──
export async function getChannelMessages(channelId, page = 0, size = 50) {
  return request(`/channels/${channelId}/messages?page=${page}&size=${size}`);
}

// Cursor-based scroll-up: pass the createdAt of the oldest message you have
export async function getMessagesBefore(channelId, before, size = 50) {
  return request(`/channels/${channelId}/messages/before?before=${encodeURIComponent(before)}&size=${size}`);
}

// ── Presence ──
export async function getGuildPresence(guildId) {
  return request(`/guilds/${guildId}/presence`);
}
```

---

### 2. WebSocket Service — STOMP + SockJS

This is the core of real-time messaging. One file, reusable everywhere:

```js
// src/services/websocket.js

import { Client } from "@stomp/stompjs";
import SockJS from "sockjs-client";

let stompClient = null;

/**
 * Connect to the WebSocket server.
 * Returns a promise that resolves when connected.
 */
export function connect(token) {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    stompClient = new Client({
      // Use SockJS as the transport
      webSocketFactory: () => new SockJS("http://localhost:8000/ws"),

      // Pass JWT as a STOMP header on CONNECT
      connectHeaders: {
        Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,
      },

      // Auto-reconnect after 5 seconds
      reconnectDelay: 5000,

      onConnect: () => {
        console.log("✅ STOMP connected");
        resolve(stompClient);
      },

      onStompError: (frame) => {
        console.error("❌ STOMP error:", frame.headers["message"]);
        reject(new Error(frame.headers["message"]));
      },

      onDisconnect: () => {
        console.log("🔌 STOMP disconnected");
      },
    });

    stompClient.activate();
  });
}

/**
 * Subscribe to a channel's messages.
 * Returns the subscription object (call .unsubscribe() to stop).
 */
export function subscribeToChannel(channelId, onMessage) {
  if (!stompClient || !stompClient.connected) {
    throw new Error("STOMP not connected");
  }

  return stompClient.subscribe(`/group/channel/${channelId}`, (message) => {
    const payload = JSON.parse(message.body);
    onMessage(payload);
  });
}

/**
 * Send a message to a channel.
 */
export function sendMessage(channelId, content, replyToId = null) {
  if (!stompClient || !stompClient.connected) {
    throw new Error("STOMP not connected");
  }

  stompClient.publish({
    destination: `/app/chat/${channelId}`,
    body: JSON.stringify({
      content,
      replyToId,
      attachmentUrl: null,
    }),
  });
}

/**
 * Disconnect cleanly.
 */
export function disconnect() {
  if (stompClient) {
    stompClient.deactivate();
    stompClient = null;
  }
}

/**
 * Check if currently connected.
 */
export function isConnected() {
  return stompClient?.connected ?? false;
}
```

